# ===========================================================================
# SECURITY — API Keys & Credentials
# Covers all common .env variants to prevent accidental key exposure.
# GEMINI_API_KEY and any other secrets must never reach version control.
# ===========================================================================
.env
.env.*
.env.local
.env.development
.env.staging
.env.production
.env.test
*.env
!.env.example
!.env.template

# uv / pip lock files that may embed index URLs with tokens
# (lock files themselves are fine, but keep this as a reminder)
# uv.lock — intentionally NOT ignored (lock files should be committed)

# ===========================================================================
# Python virtual environments
# .venv* already covers most cases from the scaffold above, but listed
# explicitly here for clarity when auditing this file.
# ===========================================================================
.venv/
.venv*/
venv/
env/
